main event: On June 29th, 1947, a civilian in Des Moines, Iowa reported observing seven dirty white saucers heading northwest, and later one heading west.
interesting points: The observer reported seeing seven saucers of a dirty white color heading northwest.
Later, the observer saw one saucer heading west.
No photographs or physical evidence were captured.
The observation was classified as a 'Other (INTELLIGENCE REPORT)'
The duration of the observation was not reported.
